When creating a Rigidbody(in scene root), it will call Node::GetOrCreateComponent to create a PhysicsWorld component in scene. Then save the scene to file, and load  again, it will show two PhysicsWorld components in scene. One is auto created when loading Rigidbody component another is loaded from file.

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5548857/5467037/16aee2c6-85f3-11e4-85c4-d4de537e7685.png)

So when call Node::GetOrCreateComponent to create a new component, it is better to move the componet at first. like this:

```
Component* Node::GetOrCreateComponent(StringHash type, CreateMode mode, unsigned id)
{
    Component* oldComponent = GetComponent(type);
    if (oldComponent)
        return oldComponent;
    else
    {
        SharedPtr<Component> newComponent(CreateComponent(type, mode, id));

        // Move new component to begin
        components_.Remove(newComponent);
        components_.Insert(0, newComponent);

        return newComponent;
    }
}
```

