This function can loop endlessly if there's an issue within the `Log::Write` function, which pushes back another log entry. This results in the list never being empty:

```
void Log::HandleEndFrame(StringHash eventType, VariantMap& eventData)
{
    MutexLock lock(logMutex_);

    // Process messages accumulated from other threads (if any)
    while (!threadMessages_.Empty())   
    {
        const StoredLogMessage& stored = threadMessages_.Front();

        if (stored.level_ != LOG_RAW)
            Write(stored.level_, stored.message_);
        else
            WriteRaw(stored.message_, stored.error_);

        threadMessages_.PopFront();
    }
}
```

If `IsMainThread` returns false and `logInstance` is valid, the log entry is pushed back into the list.

```
